  override val startShort =
    "In Tokyo, the wind carries echoes of the past through the streamlined shapes of a cityscape where ancient customs tenderly weave into the rhythm of modern life. It's the heart of spring, when the celebrated sakura trees robe themselves in soft blossoms, casting a soft pink shade across this extensive city." /
    "Here, among the easy flow of city dwellers and serene gardens, we prepare to navigate the wide network of the Tokyo metro train and Toei subway system. Our smooth travels are led by a gentle-spoken young woman whose warm smile emits a welcome as soothing as the precisely trimmed bonsai gardens." /
    "As we ready ourselves for a cultural experience with this lively city, the anticipation of discovery instills us with a comforting sense of adventure, and the engaging pace of Tokyo invites us to delve into its storied streets and hidden nooks." /
    "Our guide brings us to the Asakusa district, home to the revered Senso-ji Temple. The Tokyo subway deftly carries us to the heart of Asakusa, where history is carefully honored." /
    "As we alight from the station, we're immediately wrapped in the calming rhythm of everyday life in this historic quarter. A short walk takes us to the imposing Kaminarimon, or Thunder Gate, the commanding entrance to Senso-ji." /
    "Here, a lantern as red as the petals of ume blossoms hangs with a distinguished heft from the gate's sturdy frame, attracting locals and travelers alike with its compelling presence as an unofficial emblem of the area." /
    "Passing beneath its hefty portal, we are swept into the dynamic stream of Nakamise-dori. Our guide recounts how the Thunder Gate had seen centuries pass by its vigilant position since the temple's legendary founding in six hundred and twenty-eight." /
    "We listen, captivated, as she narrates the story of two fishermen who discovered a statue of Kannon, the goddess of mercy, in the Sumida River. This fortuitous discovery led to the construction of Senso-ji, a permanent retreat within the ever-changing cityscape of Tokyo's growth." /
    "As we amble down Nakamise-dori, the lively calls of vendors inviting visitors to look at their wares form an animated chorus. It's as if every stall unveils its own quiet tale, with ornate handcrafted fans revealing themselves at a leisurely pace, and the deep colors of fabrics from yukata and kimonos capturing our gaze with their elegant charm." /
    "The air teems with aromas, with the sweet scent of ningyoyaki tempting us to taste a slice of Tokyo's storied flavor—a discovery made even more enjoyable when we find out this confection is shaped like notable figures and temple motifs." /
    "The temple itself stands as a solid emblem of peace, its red-accented facade and pagoda reaching skywards towards a canvas washed in the softest shades of spring's ascent. Keen to take part in time-honored practices of adoration, we join others in reflective rituals, purifying at a shared water font in silent consideration, and later drifting healing incense fumes toward ourselves from a sizable cauldron." /
    "Amongst the hum of visitors and the subtle, methodical motions of prayer and thanks, we discover a soothing rhythm." /
    "Our hearts swathed in tranquility, we halt, letting ourselves be absorbed by the laughter and the easy, continuous flux of the temple's environs. Giving in to the gentle sweep of discovery, we let the precinct of Senso-ji enfold us, our inhalations syncing with the subdued pulse of Tokyo's historic core."

