    "After the immersive array of sights, sounds, and tastes at Tsukiji Outer Market, our tour glides back to Ueno Park's embrace, this time guiding us to the Tokyo National Museum's impressive façades. Established in eighteen seventy-two, the museum stands as a witness to Japanese history, arts, and culture—a collection as rich and complex as the stories of the islands themselves." /
